finaliseFor((address,uint256,uint256,uin.details: This function serves to finalise intents on the origin chain. It has been assumed that assets have been locked inside The Compact and will be available to collect. To properly collect the order details and proofs, the settler needs the solver identifier and the timestamps of the fills.

params.order: CatalystCompactOrder signed in conjunction with a Compact to form an order.
params.signatures: A signature for the sponsor and the allocator. abi.encode(bytes(sponsorSignature), bytes(allocatorSignature))

purchaseOrder(bytes32,(address,uint256,u.details: If you are buying a challenged order, ensure that you have sufficient time to prove the order or your funds may be at risk and that you purchase it within the allocated time. To purchase an order, it is required that you can produce a proper signature from the solver that signs the purchase details.

params.expiryTimestamp: Set to ensure if your transaction isn't mine quickly, you don't end up purchasing an order that you cannot prove OR is not within the timeToBuy window.
params.orderSolvedByIdentifier: Solver of the order. Is not validated, need to be correct otherwise the purchase will be wasted.

Finalises a cross-chain order on behalf of someone else

purchaseOrder(bytes32,(address,uint256,u.notice: This function is called by whoever wants to buy an order from a filler. If the order was purchased in time, then when the order is settled, the inputs will go to the purchaser instead of the original solver.
